}</script><section id="services-hero-532"><picture class="cs-bg-picture"><source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-artificial-turf-37-ee326323.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-artificial-turf-37-3f18488c.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-artificial-turf-37-91440bfb.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-artificial-turf-37-289488e3.jpeg" height="775" width="1920" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-card"><div class="cs-heading-group"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Serving Sunland Park Since 2005</span><h1 class="cs-title">Landscaping Services in <span class="cs-color">Sunland Park, NM</span></h1></div><p class="cs-text">Drought-tolerant landscape design, hardscaping, irrigation, and xeriscaping for Sunland Park and Santa Teresa. Built for rocky desert soil, new construction lots, and extreme sun exposure.</p><div class="cs-button-group"><a class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button" href="/contact/">Schedule an Estimate</a> <a class="cs-phone-button" href="tel:575-635-8883"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div></div></div></section><section id="services-intro-109"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern cs-fern-right"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern cs-fern-left"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-row"><picture class="cs-picture"><source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-sod-4-bf42d559.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-sod-4-7fb24e56.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-sod-4-64a11b13.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="Fresh sod lawn install on a new construction property in Sunland Park, NM" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-sod-4-00901243.jpeg" height="503" width="480" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Why Sunland Park</span><h2 class="cs-title">Growing with Sunland Park &amp; Santa Teresa</h2><p class="cs-text">Sunland Park sits just west of El Paso on the New Mexico side of the border, about 30 minutes from Las Cruces. The city is growing fast. Santa Teresa, right next door, is one of the fastest-growing areas in southern New Mexico with new housing developments going up every year. The Sunland Park Racetrack &amp; Casino and Mt. Cristo Rey are local landmarks that help define the area.</p><p class="cs-text">Many homes here are brand new, sitting on bare lots with no landscaping at all. Others are in established neighborhoods that need updates. Either way, the soil is rocky and sandy, the wind hits hard from the west, and the sun is intense year-round. Our crew knows these conditions and builds landscapes that hold up to all of them.</p><div class="cs-button-group"><a class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button" href="/contact/">Schedule an Estimate</a> <a class="cs-phone-button" href="tel:575-635-8883"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="13" width="13" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div></div></div></div></section><section id="areas-services-610"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> What We Do Here</span><h2 class="cs-title">Services Available in Sunland Park</h2></div><div class="cs-grid"><ul class="cs-card-group"><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-landscape-design.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Landscape Design</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Custom plans for new construction lots and established homes in Sunland Park and Santa Teresa.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/landscape-design/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-landscaping.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Landscaping &amp; Install</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Full-property planting, grading, and installation on rocky desert lots, including builder cleanup.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/landscaping/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-hardscaping.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Hardscaping &amp; Patios</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Patios, retaining walls, and walkways built on sandy desert soil with proper footings for stability.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/hardscaping/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-xeriscaping.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Xeriscaping</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Water-wise design with Agave, Red Yucca, and heat-tolerant groundcovers for full-sun Sunland Park lots.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/landscaping/xeriscaping/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-irrigation.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Irrigation &amp; Sprinkler</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Drip systems and smart controllers sized for extreme heat and the sandy, fast-draining soil in this area.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/irrigation/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-maintenance.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Landscape Maintenance</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Seasonal cleanup, pruning, irrigation checks, and wind damage repair for Sunland Park properties.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/landscape-maintenance/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li></ul><aside class="cs-area-info"><h3 class="cs-area-title">One Call, One Crew, All Six Services</h3><p class="cs-area-text">New construction homes in Sunland Park often need everything at once: design, grading, irrigation, planting, and hardscaping. Bundling under one team keeps your timeline, budget, and guarantee in a single place.</p><ul class="cs-area-bullets"><li><span class="cs-check" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" width="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M2 7.5 L5.5 11 L12 3.5"></path></svg> </span>Design-build under one roof</li><li><span class="cs-check" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" width="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M2 7.5 L5.5 11 L12 3.5"></path></svg> </span>Workmanship guarantee</li><li><span class="cs-check" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" width="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M2 7.5 L5.5 11 L12 3.5"></path></svg> </span>New-build specialists, blank-canvas experts</li></ul></aside></div></div></section><section id="areas-landmarks-620"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-row"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Where We Work</span><h2 class="cs-title">Neighborhoods &amp; Areas We Serve</h2><p class="cs-text">We cover Sunland Park, Santa Teresa, and the surrounding communities. From brand-new subdivisions off Pete Domenici Highway to established homes along Sunland Park Drive, we handle residential and commercial projects across this growing area.</p><div class="cs-button-group"><a class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button" href="/contact/">Schedule an Estimate</a> <a class="cs-phone-button" href="tel:575-635-8883"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="13" width="13" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div></div><picture class="cs-picture"><source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-artificial-turf-38-6b88ac10.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-artificial-turf-38-88e88ff9.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-artificial-turf-38-88e88ff9.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="Artificial turf lawn install in the Sunland Park, NM area" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-artificial-turf-38-3df6826b.jpeg" height="773" width="580" loading="lazy"></picture></div><ul class="cs-neighborhoods"><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Sunland Park Proper <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88063</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">Established neighborhoods near the racetrack and Mt. Cristo Rey. A mix of older homes needing landscape updates and newer infill construction.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Santa Teresa <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88008</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">Rapidly growing with new housing developments and an industrial park. Most homes are brand new on bare lots, ready for full landscape installs from scratch.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Anapra Area <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88063</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">A community on the western edge of Sunland Park with strong wind exposure and rocky desert terrain. Windbreak plantings and erosion control are common needs here.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">McNutt Road Corridor <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88063</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">Residential and commercial properties along one of the main routes through Sunland Park. Curb appeal projects and parking lot landscaping are popular in this corridor.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Sunland Park Drive Area <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88063</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">The central commercial and residential strip. Businesses and homeowners here need landscapes that handle heavy foot traffic and full desert sun.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Pete Domenici Highway Corridor <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88008</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">New subdivisions and commercial development along the highway connecting Santa Teresa to Las Cruces. Clean-slate lots with no existing vegetation.</p></li></ul></div></section><section id="services-why-353" class="cs-why-light"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper">Local Know-How</span><h2 class="cs-title">What Makes Sunland Park Landscapes Different</h2><p class="cs-intro">Sunland Park sits at a lower elevation than Las Cruces, so temperatures run slightly warmer. The soil is rocky and sandy. Many new construction lots are covered in builder debris. Wind from the west is strong and constant. Every landscape we build here is designed around these realities.</p></div><div class="cs-gallery" aria-hidden="true"><picture class="cs-picture cs-picture-1"><source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-29-4cc279a6.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-29-f56cae6c.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-29-f56cae6c.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-29-f8becb2e.jpeg" height="594" width="460" loading="lazy"></picture><picture class="cs-picture cs-picture-2"><source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-artificial-turf-39-2e5a4491.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-artificial-turf-39-a49300e8.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-artificial-turf-39-a49300e8.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-artificial-turf-39-a161f655.jpeg" height="439" width="330" loading="lazy"></picture></div><ul class="cs-feature-list"><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Rocky, Sandy Desert Soil</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Sunland Park soil is sandy with plenty of rock. It drains fast, which means water runs right through before roots can absorb it. We build planting beds with amended soil and use drip irrigation to keep water in the root zone longer.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Construction Debris in Soil</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Builders often leave concrete chunks, rebar, and rubble buried in the yard. On new construction lots, we excavate and clean the soil before planting. Skipping this step leads to drainage problems and dead plants within a year.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Strong Western Wind</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Sunland Park gets hit by strong winds from the west, especially in spring. We plant windbreak rows using Afghan Pine and Desert Willow, and we anchor gravel mulch to prevent it from blowing away.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Extreme Sun, Zero Shade</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Most Sunland Park lots have no existing trees or shade. We design for full sun from the start, using heat-loving species like Agave, Ocotillo, and Texas Sage. For shade, we plant fast-growing Chilean Mesquite or Chitalpa in strategic spots.</p></li></ul><a class="cs-quote-button" href="/contact/">Schedule an Estimate</a></div></section><section id="testimonials-515" class="cs-reviews-carousel"><picture class="cs-bg-leaves"><source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="/assets/images/leaves-pattern-5f48081d.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/leaves-pattern-edeab06b.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/leaves-pattern-03e85c27.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/leaves-pattern-8329654d.jpeg" height="1072" width="1920" loading="lazy"></picture><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Testimonials</span><h2 class="cs-title">Let’s Talk About Your Outdoor Vision</h2></div><div class="cs-controls"><button class="cs-arrow cs-arrow-prev" aria-label="Previous reviews" type="button" data-reviews-prev=""><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M15 18l-6-6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></button> <button class="cs-arrow cs-arrow-next" aria-label="Next reviews" type="button" data-reviews-next=""><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M9 6l6 6-6 6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></button></div></div><ul class="cs-card-group" data-reviews-track=""><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars" role="img"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">David was incredibly knowledgeable and helpful. He patiently answered all of my questions about the plants and trees around my home and provided valuable insights into the issues I was facing. His friendly demeanor and expertise made the experience enjoyable and informative. I highly recommend him</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Alexis Silva</span> <span class="cs-role">a year ago</span></div><a class="cs-google-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103948667181155023139/reviews" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars" role="img"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">We had a great experience with David. We used him for one of our rental properties in Las Cruces and will definitely be using him again for the next one. Everything from start to finish was professional and timely. Highly recommend.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Travis Boyle</span> <span class="cs-role">a year ago</span></div><a class="cs-google-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108997149124684397289/reviews" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars" role="img"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">Brainard's Greenscapes recently revamped my backyard with rock landscaping. I couldn't be happier with how the project turned out. From start to finish David's team was professional, punctual, and courteous. They helped me select the the right materials and offered additional design ideas. The quality of work was EXCELLENT. I highly recommend David's team to all homeowners in Las Cruces looking for reliable landscaping company. The picture below is of my backyard 1 year later and there is still no weeds! I can't think Braindard's Greenscapes enough.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Matthew Lee</span> <span class="cs-role">a year ago</span></div><a class="cs-google-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112275232644298872770/reviews" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars" role="img"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">I had a sprinkler emergency and David came out immediately; found an effective solution to get me through until the major repairs could be made; and took care to make sure my house wasn't without water in the meantime. I am so grateful for his kindness and professionalism. He demonstrated considerable expertise and decisive decision making that got me through this emergencies with minimal stress. He is trustworthy and will be the first one I'll call on any future sprinkler needs.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Jennifer Wees-Schkade</span> <span class="cs-role">2 years ago</span></div><a class="cs-google-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113879630740524577871/reviews" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars" role="img"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">Brainard’s Greenscapes is a top notch business. I have called on them on several occasions to fix issues with my irrigation system and for new projects. David, the owner, is a sincere, honest individual, who cares about his business and his customers. His employees are also kind and always professional. They are punctual and complete the job as promised and clean up after they are done. I am very pleased with David and his company and have recommended him to my neighbor, who is also a widow because I know he is honest and will not take advantage of her. David is a good guy and I recommend that you give him a call and see for yourself.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">George Rodriguez</span> <span class="cs-role">6 years ago</span></div><a class="cs-google-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113926776793747685994/reviews" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li></ul></div></section><section id="areas-projects-630"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Case Studies</span><h2 class="cs-title">Sunland Park Project Showcase</h2></div><ul class="cs-project-group"><li class="cs-project"><picture class="cs-project-picture"><source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-artificial-turf-40-5019e6b9.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-artificial-turf-40-565e96c1.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-artificial-turf-40-58ba09ce.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="New construction artificial turf install in Santa Teresa, NM" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-artificial-turf-40-3942ae81.jpeg" height="411" width="616" loading="lazy"></picture><h3 class="cs-project-title">Santa Teresa New-Build Landscape</h3><p class="cs-project-text">Complete landscape from bare dirt: builder debris removal, drip irrigation, xeriscape planting, and a flagstone patio.</p></li><li class="cs-project"><picture class="cs-project-picture"><source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-36-9bbf5497.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-36-d9b5189a.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-36-97614fbe.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="Native windbreak and xeriscape project in Sunland Park, NM" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-36-496e3475.jpeg" height="411" width="616" loading="lazy"></picture><h3 class="cs-project-title">Sunland Park Windbreak &amp; Xeriscape</h3><p class="cs-project-text">Installed a multi-row windbreak with Afghan Pine along the west side and a low-water xeriscape front yard with gravel mulch.</p></li></ul></div></section><section id="faq-506"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> FAQ</span><h2 class="cs-title">Sunland Park Landscaping FAQ</h2></div><ul class="cs-faq-list"><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Do you serve the new Santa Teresa developments?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Yes. We work in all Santa Teresa subdivisions, including the newer developments along Pete Domenici Highway. Most of these homes are on bare lots, and we handle everything from builder debris removal to full landscape installation.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How much does landscaping cost for a new construction home?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>It depends on lot size, design choices, and whether you need hardscaping. A typical new-build xeriscape with drip irrigation on a standard Sunland Park lot starts around $5,000 to $8,000. Full landscape packages with patios and retaining walls run higher. We provide free on-site estimates so you get an exact number before any work begins.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">What is the best time to install landscaping on a new build?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Fall through early spring (October to March) is ideal. Cooler temperatures let plants establish roots before the brutal summer heat arrives. We install year-round, but fall planting cuts first-year water use roughly in half. Hardscaping can go in any time of year.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Do you offer landscape maintenance plans?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Yes. We offer monthly and seasonal maintenance plans that include pruning, irrigation checks, weed control, and gravel raking. This is especially useful for Sunland Park homeowners who want to keep a new landscape looking sharp without doing the work themselves.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How do I keep landscaping alive in extreme heat?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>It starts with the right plant selection. We choose species that are proven in Sunland Park’s heat, like Agave, Ocotillo, Desert Willow, and Texas Sage. A properly designed drip irrigation system is essential. We also use 3 to 4 inches of gravel mulch to insulate roots and reduce soil temperature.</p></div></details></li></ul></div></section><section id="areas-stats-640"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><div class="cs-heading-col"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Our Coverage Area</span><h2 class="cs-title">Where We Work in Sunland Park</h2></div><div class="cs-copy-col"><p class="cs-text">On the map below: our Sunland Park service area, covering Sunland Park proper, Santa Teresa, Anapra, the McNutt Road corridor, Sunland Park Drive, and the Pete Domenici Highway corridor.</p><a class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button" href="/contact/">Schedule an Estimate</a></div></div><div class="cs-map" aria-label="Map of Sunland Park, NM service area"><iframe allowfullscreen="" height="430" loading="lazy" referrerpolicy="no-referrer-when-downgrade" src="https://www.google.com/maps?q=Sunland+Park+NM&amp;z=13&amp;output=embed" title="Map of Sunland Park, NM service area" width="1280"></iframe></div><ul class="cs-stats"><li class="cs-stat"><span class="cs-stat-number">500+</span> <span class="cs-stat-label">Valley Projects</span></li><li class="cs-stat"><span class="cs-stat-number">19+</span> <span class="cs-stat-label">Years in the Valley</span></li><li class="cs-stat"><span class="cs-stat-number">5/5</span> <span class="cs-stat-label">Average Rating</span></li><li class="cs-stat"><span class="cs-stat-number">100%</span> <span class="cs-stat-label">Quality Guarantee</span></li></ul></div></section><section id="areas-neighbors-660"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Nearby</span><h2 class="cs-title">Neighboring Areas We Serve</h2><p class="cs-text">We also handle landscape projects in nearby Mesilla Valley communities just minutes away.</p></div><ul class="cs-neighbors"><li class="cs-neighbor"><a class="cs-neighbor-link" href="/service-areas/anthony-nm/"><span class="cs-neighbor-name">Landscaping in Anthony, NM</span><span class="cs-neighbor-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></li><li class="cs-neighbor"><a class="cs-neighbor-link" href="/service-areas/las-cruces-nm/"><span class="cs-neighbor-name">Landscaping in Las Cruces, NM</span><span class="cs-neighbor-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></li><li class="cs-neighbor"><a class="cs-neighbor-link" href="/service-areas/mesilla-park-nm/"><span class="cs-neighbor-name">Landscaping in Mesilla Park, NM</span><span class="cs-neighbor-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></li><li class="cs-neighbor"><a class="cs-neighbor-link" href="/service-areas/mesilla-nm/"><span class="cs-neighbor-name">Landscaping in Mesilla, NM</span><span class="cs-neighbor-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></li></ul></div></section><section id="lets-talk-318"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/s